[34m│[0m ## IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference) Attack Playbook                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > **IMPORTANT:** All payloads in this playbook are EXAMPLES that must be     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m MODIFIED for your specific target. Replace placeholders like `{ID}`,         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `{PARAMETER}`, `{TARGET_URL}`, `{OBJECT_ID}` with actual values. Adapt       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m techniques based on:                                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Target's object reference patterns (numeric, UUID, hashed, etc.)         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Parameter names and locations                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Authorization checks and bypass methods                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Discovered object relationships                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > IDOR occurs when an application provides direct access to objects based on [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m user-supplied input without proper authorization checks.                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Core Concept                                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Example:**                                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Original: https://example.com/profile?user_id=123                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Attack:   https://example.com/profile?user_id=124                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m If application doesn't verify the logged-in user has permission to view      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m user_id=124, attacker can access other users' data.                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Testing Methodology                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **1. Numeric Value Parameter:**                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Increment/decrement numeric IDs: `287789`, `287790`, `287791`              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test hexadecimal: `0x4642d`, `0x4642e`, `0x4642f`                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test Unix epoch timestamps: `1695574808`, `1695575098`                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **2. Common Identifiers Parameter:**                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Guessable names: `john`, `doe`, `john.doe`                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Email addresses: `john.doe@mail.com`                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Base64 encoded: `am9obi5kb2VAbWFpbC5jb20=`                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **3. Weak Pseudo Random Number Generator:**                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - **UUID/GUID v1:** Predictable if creation time known:                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `95f6e264-bb00-11ec-8833-00155d01ef00`                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - **MongoDB Object IDs:** Predictable structure:                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m   - 4-byte: seconds since Unix epoch                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m   - 3-byte: machine identifier                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m   - 2-byte: process id                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m   - 3-byte: counter (starts random)                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m   - Example: `5ae9b90a2c144b9def01ec37`                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **4. Hashed Parameter:**                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - MD5: `098f6bcd4621d373cade4e832627b4f6`                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - SHA1: `a94a8fe5ccb19ba61c4c0873d391e987982fbbd3`                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - SHA2: `9f86d081884c7d659a2feaa0c55ad015a3bf4f1b2b0b822cd15d6c15b0f00a08`   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test if hash is predictable (e.g., `sha1(username)`, `md5(email)`)         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **5. Wildcard Parameter:**                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Test wildcards instead of specific IDs:                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m GET /api/users/* HTTP/1.1                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m GET /api/users/% HTTP/1.1                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m GET /api/users/_ HTTP/1.1                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m GET /api/users/. HTTP/1.1                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Some backends might return all users' data.                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### IDOR Bypass Techniques                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **HTTP Method Change:**                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Change `POST → PUT` or `GET → POST`                                        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Some endpoints have different authorization checks                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Content Type Change:**                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Change `XML → JSON` or vice versa                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Different parsers might have different validation                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Array Wrapping:**                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Original: {"id":19}                                                          [34m│[0m
